description:

## ‚úÖ Ce que fait ce mod√®le

## üß© Comment cela fonctionne (n≈ìud par n≈ìud)

## üõ†Ô∏è Instructions de configuration (√† partir du JSON)

3. Dans vos n≈ìuds **Google Sheets**, s√©lectionnez votre identifiant et la feuille/tab cible.

> Remplacez tous les exemples d'ID/URLs de feuille par **les v√¥tres** (√©vitez de publier des ID priv√©s).

---

### 2) Obtenir un jeton Bearer D&B (Authentification de base ‚Üí `/v3/token`) ‚Äî N≈ìud de jeton dynamique optionnel

> ‚ö†Ô∏è **S√©curit√© :** Ne pas coder en dur les jetons. Pr√©f√©rez les identifiants ou r√©cup√©rez dynamiquement.

---

### 3) Appeler les blocs de donn√©es D&B (utiliser l'authentification par en-t√™te ou le jeton dynamique)
**N≈ìud :** `Infos D&B` (HTTP Request)  
- **Authentification :** Authentification par en-t√™te (recommand√©e)  
- **URL :**
  ```
  https://plus.dnb.com/v1/data/duns/{{ $json.duns }}?blockIDs=paymentinsight_L4_v1&tradeUp=hq&customerReference=customer%20reference%20text&orderReason=6332
  ```
- **En-t√™tes :**

  - Si vous n'utilisez pas un identifiant d'authentification par en-t√™te stock√©, d√©finissez :  
    `Authorization = Bearer {{$node["Obtenir le jeton Bearer1"].json["access_token"]}}`

> `{{ $json.duns }}` est r√©solu √† partir de la ligne actuelle fournie par **Obtenir des entreprises**.

---

### 4) Mapper Paydex et mettre √† jour dans Google Sheets
- **Garder le score (D√©finir)**  
  - Champ **`Paydex`** (Nombre) :  
    ```
    {{$json.organization.businessTrading[0].summary[0].paydexScoreHistory[0].paydexScore}}
    ```
- **Ajouter √† g-sheets (Google Sheets)**  
  - **Op√©ration :** `Ajouter ou Mettre √† jour`  
  - **Colonne de correspondance :** `duns`  
  - **Mapping des colonnes :**  
    - `duns = {{ $('Obtenir des entreprises').item.json.duns }}`

---

## üß™ Liste de contr√¥le des tests
- Ajoutez quelques lignes DUNS de test (laissez `Complete` vide).  
- Ex√©cutez le flux de travail et confirmez que **Seulement de nouvelles lignes** passe les √©l√©ments attendus.  
- V√©rifiez que **Infos D&B** renvoie des donn√©es d'informations de paiement.  
- Confirmez que **Paydex** est d√©fini et que la ligne est mise √† jour avec `Complete = Oui`.

## üîê S√©curit√© et meilleures pratiques
- Stockez les secrets dans **Identifiants** (Authentification par en-t√™te HTTP/Authentification de base).  
- √âvitez de publier de vrais ID de feuille ou jetons dans des captures d'√©cran/notes.

## ü©π D√©pannage

parameters.content:
### Enrich DUNS rows in Google Sheets with Dun & Bradstreet Data Blocks (Bearer Token ‚Üí Fetch ‚Üí Upsert)

Automate company enrichment in **Google Sheets** using **Dun & Bradstreet**. This workflow reads DUNS from a sheet, gets a D&B **Bearer token** (Basic Auth ‚Üí `/v3/token`), calls **Data Blocks** (`/v1/data/duns/...`), pulls **Paydex** from the response, and **append-or-updates** the sheet. A **Filter** node skips rows already marked `Complete`.

## Setup Instructions

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Connect Google Sheets (OAuth2)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Google Sheets (OAuth2)**  
2. Sign in with your Google account and grant access  
3. In your workflow‚Äôs **Google Sheets** nodes, select this credential  
4. Use/prepare a sheet with at least: **duns**, **paydex**, **Complete**

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Get a D&B Bearer Token (Basic Auth ‚Üí `/v3/token`)
1. Add (or enable) an **HTTP Request** node named `Get Bearer Token1`  
2. Configure:  
   - **Authentication:** Basic Auth (your **D&B username** & **password**)  
   - **Method:** `POST`  
   - **URL:** `https://plus.dnb.com/v3/token`  
   - **Body Parameters:** `grant_type = client_credentials`  
   - **Headers:** `Accept = application/json`  
3. **Execute** ‚Äî the response includes `access_token` you will reference later

> ‚ö†Ô∏è **Security:** Don‚Äôt hardcode tokens. Always fetch the token and reference it dynamically.

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Call D&B Data Blocks (use dynamic Bearer token)
1. Add an **HTTP Request** node named `Data Blocks`  
2. Configure:  
   - **Authentication:** None  
   - **Method:** `GET`  
   - **URL:**  
     ```
     https://plus.dnb.com/v1/data/duns/{{ $json.duns }}?blockIDs=paymentinsight_L4_v1&tradeUp=hq&customerReference=customer%20reference%20text&orderReason=6332
     ```
     > `{{ $json.duns }}` resolves per row from the Google Sheets node.  
   - **Headers:**  
     - `Accept = application/json`  
     - `Authorization = Bearer {{$node["Get Bearer Token1"].json["access_token"]}}`
       > This pulls the token from the token node‚Äôs output.

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Map Paydex and Upsert to Google Sheets
1. **Set** node (`Edit Fields1`) ‚Üí create a field:  
   - **Name:** `Paydex`  
   - **Value (Number):**  
     ```
     {{$json.organization.businessTrading[0].summary[0].paydexScoreHistory[0].paydexScore}}
     ```
2. **Google Sheets ‚Üí Append or Update**  
   - **Operation:** `Append or Update`  
   - **Matching column:** `duns`  
   - **Columns mapping:**  
     - `duns = {{ $('Get row(s) in sheet2').item.json.duns }}`  
     - `paydex = {{ $json.Paydex }}`  
     - `Complete = Yes`

---


## üì¨ Contact  
Need help customizing this (e.g., enriching more fields, normalizing responses, or bulk-processing large sheets)?

- üìß **robert@ynteractive.com**  
- üîó **https://www.linkedin.com/in/robert-breen-29429625/**  
- üåê **https://ynteractive.com**

### üìë Fetch Company Report from D&B (PDF/JSON)

1. Add a new **HTTP Request** node and name it `D&B Report`  
2. Configure it as follows:  
   - **Authentication:** Header Auth (use your D&B credential in n8n)  
   - **Method:** `GET`  
   - **URL:**  
     ```
     https://plus.dnb.com/v1/reports/duns/804735132?productId=birstd&inLanguage=en-US&reportFormat=PDF&orderReason=6332&tradeUp=hq&customerReference=customer%20reference%20text
     ```  
     > Replace the sample DUNS (`804735132`) with a dynamic reference like `{{ $json.duns }}` if pulling from input data.  
3. Under **Headers**, add:  
   - `Accept = application/json`  
4. Execute the node ‚Äî you‚Äôll receive a **company report** from D&B (JSON metadata, or PDF depending on `reportFormat`).  

‚úÖ You can route the output to **Google Drive**, **email**, or save it to a database for compliance and reporting.

### üîë Set up D&B Auth HTTP Request node

1. Add a new **HTTP Request** node in your workflow  
2. Configure it as follows:  
   - **Authentication:** Basic Auth (use your D&B **username** and **password**)  
   - **Method:** `POST`  
   - **URL:** `https://plus.dnb.com/v3/token`  
3. Under **Body Parameters**, add:  
   - `grant_type = client_credentials`  
4. Under **Headers**, add:  
   - `Accept = application/json`  
5. Execute the node ‚Äî the response will include an **access_token**  
6. Use this token in downstream requests with:  
   - `Authorization: Bearer {{$json["access_token"]}}`

### 3) Connect Google Sheets (OAuth2)

1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Google Sheets (OAuth2)**  
2. Sign in with your Google account and **grant access**.  
3. In your workflow‚Äôs **Google Sheets** node (e.g., *Append or Update*), select this spreadsheet and tab:  
   - **Spreadsheet URL:** https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1wlzNuN16KfD72owWceXmTvVulGBplMBv3c1DlsSayHI/edit?gid=0#gid=0  
   - **Spreadsheet ID:** `1wlzNuN16KfD72owWceXmTvVulGBplMBv3c1DlsSayHI`  
   - **Tab (gid):** `0` *(usually ‚ÄúSheet1‚Äù)*  
4. (Optional) Set **Operation** to **Append or Update** and choose a **Matching Column** (e.g., `duns`) to prevent duplicates.
